    "url": "https://x.com/oesnadaki/status/2070504369569608009",
    "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/oesnadaki/status/2070504369569608009",
    "text": ".@elastic is cutting roughly 7 percent of its staff, impacting about 300 employees as it reorganizes its engineering department. CEO Ash Kulkarni is explicitly citing AI and automation as the drivers, claiming these technologies allow the firm to maintain leaner operations while the nature of development work evolves. The move highlights a growing trend where healthy financials—including a 16 percent revenue jump to $451 million—no longer protect technical roles from displacement by automated workflows. By flattening its hierarchy into three core areas, $ESTC is betting it can simplify operations without losing the momentum gained from its recent return to open-source standards. Management still expects total headcount to grow this year, signaling a strategic pivot toward customer-facing sales over traditional engineering growth.",
